    "body": "For the record: we may want to produce better error messages for these cases, but those are all invalid uses of ``memoryguard``: The argument to ``memoryguard`` defines the currently assumed start of \"general purpose memory\", so it will always be a low value - and a value beyond 2^32 for it makes no sense.\r\n\r\nBut yeah, this should be caught in Yul analysis rather than hit an assertion in Yul codegen.",
